And so nothing bad was happening

00:25:49.281 --> 00:25:50.583 align:middle line:84%
because everyone was
having a good time.

00:25:50.583 --> 00:25:53.052 align:middle line:84%
So you had to come up with
something to fill your hour,

00:25:53.052 --> 00:25:54.620 align:middle line:90%
so you came up with that.

00:25:54.620 --> 00:25:55.988 align:middle line:90%
Oh, brilliant."

00:25:55.988 --> 00:26:00.726 align:middle line:84%
And of course, by understanding
with curiosity that whether

00:26:00.726 --> 00:26:02.762 align:middle line:84%
or not something is
true or not for you --

00:26:02.762 --> 00:26:05.731 align:middle line:84%
because it might not be true
for you that you're going

00:26:05.731 --> 00:26:07.633 align:middle line:84%
to get breast cancer, it
might not be true for you

00:26:07.633 --> 00:26:09.702 align:middle line:84%
that what you're eating is bad
for you, it might not be true

00:26:09.702 --> 00:26:11.804 align:middle line:84%
for you, you know,
all of these things --

00:26:11.804 --> 00:26:14.907 align:middle line:84%
knowing what is true for
you means that you can feel

00:26:14.907 --> 00:26:18.210 align:middle line:84%
so much less stress
and feel much happier.

00:26:18.210 --> 00:26:20.713 align:middle line:84%
And again, when it
comes to relationships,

00:26:20.713 --> 00:26:22.381 align:middle line:84%
when you know what's
true for you,

00:26:22.381 --> 00:26:25.251 align:middle line:84%
when you know what you value
and where your values are,

00:26:25.251 --> 00:26:27.620 align:middle line:84%
and you use your values
as compass, then you know

00:26:27.620 --> 00:26:31.190 align:middle line:84%
who to make friends with because
you know who resonates with you

00:26:31.190 --> 00:26:33.025 align:middle line:84%
and you know who you
can connect with.

00:26:33.025 --> 00:26:36.595 align:middle line:84%
So really the book is kind
of like a peaceful revolution

00:26:36.595 --> 00:26:40.900 align:middle line:84%
from thinking to knowing but in
the world, not in your bedroom,

00:26:40.900 --> 00:26:42.468 align:middle line:90%
not through meditation --

00:26:42.468 --> 00:26:45.638 align:middle line:84%
in the world because
curiosity is a meditation.

00:26:45.638 --> 00:26:47.373 align:middle line:90%
So you travel a lot.

00:26:47.373 --> 00:26:49.975 align:middle line:84%
Yeah. So it's like you know
when you go to a new place

00:26:49.975 --> 00:26:52.011 align:middle line:84%
and you're, like, looking at the
tops of buildings and you're,

00:26:52.011 --> 00:26:54.013 align:middle line:84%
like, looking at the cracks on
the pavement and you're going,

00:26:54.013 --> 00:26:55.981 align:middle line:84%
"This is really hot, and it's
England, and it's bizarre."

00:26:55.981 --> 00:26:57.683 align:middle line:84%
And then there, oh,
you're in another country

00:26:57.683 --> 00:26:59.852 align:middle line:84%
and it's freezing
cold or the smells

00:26:59.852 --> 00:27:00.986 align:middle line:90%
and things -- it's so different.

00:27:00.986 --> 00:27:01.721 align:middle line:90%
And you're curious.

00:27:01.721 --> 00:27:03.489 align:middle line:90%
And then if you notice

00:27:03.489 --> 00:27:05.458 align:middle line:84%
